ate interactions, the concept can also be applied to other problems, such as, the impact of aerosols on air quality, or the study of cloud-climate forcing and feedbacks.",,"Air quality; Algorithms; Climate change; Climatology; Clouds; Data mining; Data recording; Environmental impact; Information retrieval; Remote sensing; Climate impacts; Data integration; Environmental interactions; Multisensor algorithm; Atmospheric aerosols",,,,,,"Ackerman, T.P., Integrating and interpreting aerosol observations and models within the PARAGON framework (2004) Bull. Amer. Meteor. Soc., 85, pp. 1523-1533. , Coauthors; Baltensperger, U., (2003) WMO/GAW Aerosol Measurement Procedures: Guidelines and Recommendations, 1178, p. 72. , WMO Tech. Doc. Coauthors; Charlson, R.J., Extending atmospheric aerosol measurements to the global scale (2001) IGAC Newsl., 25, pp. 11-14. , International Global Atmospheric Chemistry Project; Demerjian, K.L., A review of national monitoring networks in North America (2000) Atmos. Environ., 34, pp. 1861-1884; Diner, D.J., Using the PARAGON framework to establish an accurate, consistent, and cohesive long-term aerosol record (2004) Bull. Amer. Meteor. Soc., 85, pp. 1535-1548. , Coauthors; (2001) Tropospheric Aerosol Program - Program Plan, p. 98. , DOE, U.S. Department of Energy Rep. DOE/SC-0034; Duce, R.A., (1993) Protecting Visibility in National Parks and Wilderness Areas, p. 316. , Coauthors, National Academy Press; Heintzenberg, J., Graf, H.-F., Charlson, R.J., Warneck, P., Climate forcing and the physicochemical life cycle of the atmospheric aerosol - Why do we need an integrated, interdisciplinary global research programme? (1996) Beitr. Phys. Atmos., 69, pp. 261-271; Kahn, R.A., Aerosol data sources and their roles within PARAGON (2004) Bull. Amer. Meteor. Soc., 85, pp. 1511-1522. , Coauthors; Kaufman, Y.J., Nakajima, T., Effect of Amazon smoke on cloud microphysics and albedo - Analysis from satellite imagery (1993) J. Appl. Meteor., 32, pp. 729-74